title: Counties won by McCain in the Florida Republican Primary, Florida by Counties, January 30th 2008
name: Counties won by McCain in the Florida Republican Primary, Florida by Counties, January 30th 2008
description:
The original data for the map is from Florida's Dept. of Elections website http://enight.dos.state.fl.us/ posted as of 4:51 AM on 30th January, 2008.  
The share of votes for McCain, Romney, Giuliani and Huckabee were computed along with the difference in share of votes between the top two contender, 
McCain and Romney. McCain won the "winner take all" primary by 36% (~689,000 votes) to Romney's 31% (~593,000). McCain gets 57 delegates and is now the front-runner in GOP. McCain won most of his votes in Middle and Southern part of the state. Look for data/map on the Geocommons that show where Romney and Huckabee got more votes than McCain as well as any other Republican candidate on the ballot.
